  <description type="morphology">Plants perennial, with stout, woody caudices; periderm beige to reddish when dried,
        1–20 mm. Stems 5–40 cm. Leaves: basal leaves flaring at base into broad, membranous sheath,
        or sheath absent, blade linear to linear-lanceolate or lanceolate, 5–18 × 0.3–1.4 cm, apex
        acute; cauline leaves sessile or petiolate, blade linear to lanceolate, 1–4 × 0.5–1 cm, apex
        acute. Inflorescences multibracteate; bracts linear to subulate, 5–10 mm, apex acute.
        Flowers 10–18 mm diam.; sepals 6–12 mm, apex acute; petals white or pink to bright rose with
        yellow blotches at base, or white, 10–14 × 4–10 mm; ovules 6. Seeds 2–6, 2–3 mm diam., shiny
        and smooth to tuberculate; elaiosome 1–2 mm. 2n = 32.</description>
